surveyor_full_name: Nathaniel Legall; Matthew Perry, Mary Claridge; Claire Trapp

additional_surveyor_notes: stop boards on Catcott Lows removed two days prior to survey in order to equalise water. Heavy flow towards ditch. 50+ minnow, 50+ roach.
Ballerina skirt on reserve side of Catcott Lows set in wrong position. Net with one corner on stop boards. 90+ minnow, 4 tench, 10+ stick insects, water boatmen, mollusca sp. Damselfly nymph.

Catcott GF = 20+ mollusca, 5 worms, 40+ minnow, 5 stickleback, 1 roach. Catcott Lows = 5+ damselfly nymphs, 30+ freshwater shrimps, 40+ mollusca spp. 5+ arachnidae. 1 minnow casualty, 1 stickleback casualty.

Catcott GF = 6 minnow, 45 mollusca sp., 5 tench, 50+ freshwater shrimp, 5+ leach. Catcottt Lows = 1 common newt, 1 damselfly nymph,  1 water scorpion, 5 water boatman, 1 damselfly nymph, 1 stick insect, beetle larvae, 36 freshwater shrimp, 11 mollusca sp.
